context: <b5_0><b6_0><b9_0>Praça dos Três Poderes (Portuguese for <a0_0>Square of the Three Powers<a0_0/>)<b9_0/><b6_0/><b5_0/> is a plaza in Brasília. The name is derived from the encounter of <a1_0><b7_0>the three federal branches around the plaza<b7_0/><a1_0/>: the Executive, represented by the Palácio do Planalto (presidential office); the Legislative, represented by the National Congress (<a4_0>Congresso Nacional<a4_0/>); and the Judicial branch, represented by the Supreme Federal Court (<a2_0>Supremo Tribunal Federal<a2_0/>). It is a tourist attraction in Brasília, designed by <a3_0><b8_0>Lúcio Costa and Oscar Niemeyer<b8_0/><a3_0/> as a place where the three branches would meet harmoniously.
